And suddenly, three days before Luzhin's departure for Berlin, one little thing happened that did not exactly change her attitude to Luzhin but vaguely moved her. The three of them had gone out for a stroll. It was a still August evening with a magnificent sunset, like a mangled blood-orange pressed out to the very last drop. 'I feel a bit chilly,' she said. 'Bring me something to put on.' And the daughter nodded her head, said 'uh-huh' through the stalk of grass she was sucking and lef